@NODE MAIN2 "DIZ-Ed Gadget Descriptions..."
                              -------------------
                               @{" Clear       (X)" LINK MAINGAD1}
                               @{" Insert Line (I)" LINK MAINGAD2}
                               @{" Delete Line (D)" LINK MAINGAD3}
                               @{" Center Line (C)" LINK MAINGAD4}
                               @{" Insert      (N)" LINK MAINGAD5}
                               @{" CursorX     n/a" LINK MAINGAD6}
                               @{" CursorY     n/a" LINK MAINGAD7}
                              -------------------
@ENDNODE
*******************************************************************************
@NODE MAINGAD1 "DIZ-Ed Gadget Description - CLEAR"

         @{b}Gadget Name: @{ub}Clear
 @{b}Keyboard Equivalent: @{ub}<CTRL>-X


 @{b}Function:@{ub}

 This gadget simply clears the display.  However it will not clear any
 current file affiliation; this is done with the @{" New Project " LINK MENU1} menu item.

@ENDNODE
*******************************************************************************
@NODE MAINGAD2 "DIZ-Ed Gadget Description - INSERT LINE"

         @{b}Gadget Name: @{ub}Insert Line
 @{b}Keyboard Equivalent: @{ub}<CTRL>-I


 @{b}Function:@{ub}

 As  might  be ascertained, this button shifts everything ON and BELOW the
 current line down one row.  Contents of the last row will be lost.

@ENDNODE
*******************************************************************************
@NODE MAINGAD3 "DIZ-Ed Gadget Description - DELETE LINE"

         @{b}Gadget Name: @{ub}Delete Line
 @{b}Keyboard Equivalent: @{ub}<CTRL>-D


 @{b}Function:@{ub}

 This will delete the current line, causing all text below to shift up one
 line taking its place.

@ENDNODE
*******************************************************************************
@NODE MAINGAD4 "DIZ-Ed Gadget Description - CENTER LINE"

         @{b}Gadget Name: @{ub}Center Line
 @{b}Keyboard Equivalent: @{ub}<CTRL>-C


 @{b}Function:@{ub}

 This will center the contents of the current line.

@ENDNODE
*******************************************************************************
@NODE MAINGAD5 "DIZ-Ed Gadget Description - INSERT"

         @{b}Gadget Name: @{ub}Insert
 @{b}Keyboard Equivalent: @{ub}<CTRL>-I


 @{b}Function:@{ub}

 The  state  of this checkbox gadget determines whether characters entered
 will shift forward those following the cursor.  Those characters inserted
 past the right border will be lost.

@ENDNODE
*******************************************************************************
@NODE MAINGAD6 "DIZ-Ed Gadget Description - CURSORX"

         @{b}Gadget Name: @{ub}CursorX
 @{b}Keyboard Equivalent: @{ub}n/a


 @{b}Function:@{ub}

 This field displays the current column number of the cursor.

@ENDNODE
*******************************************************************************
@NODE MAINGAD7 "DIZ-Ed Gadget Description - CURSORY"

         @{b}Gadget Name: @{ub}CursorY
 @{b}Keyboard Equivalent: @{ub}n/a


 @{b}Function:@{ub}

 This field displays the current row number of the cursor.

@ENDNODE
